==In popular culture==
A fictionalized version of SBX-1, armed with "Interceptor" [[anti-ballistic missile]]s, is used as the setting for the 2022 action drama film ''[[Interceptor (film)|Interceptor]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/interceptor-movie-trailer-netflix/|title=Interceptor Trailer: First Look at Matthew Reilly's Netflix Action Movie|publisher=screenrant.com|date=5 May 2022|access-date=6 June 2022}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|id=OQSoII4Bj1o|title=Netflix: Interceptor (Official trailer)}}</ref>

The SBX-1 has become known to locals of [[Oahu]] as the "[[Golf ball|Golf Ball]]" or the "Pearl of Pearl Harbor" due to its color and shape.<ref name=":0" />

An SBX-1 was credited with detecting a mysterious missile launch in the 2025 movie [[A House of Dynamite]]

